<br>
But what we can do is try and make it better.<br>
<br>
Lets see, approximately 100,000 people in jail for longer than 20 year sentences.<br>
40 thousand a year to keep them in jail.<br>
<br>
thats 4 billion a year just for those with sentences longer than 20 years (the average is 5-10 years)<br>
<br>
No with that 4 billion a year, its NOT being spent on any social programs. If we didnt have to spend it on life criminals, then we could improve the lot of people who would statistically end up in jail, thus preventing unfair trials.<br>
<br>
See, we are in a catch-22 situation. We see a problem, but we cant afford to fix it, so the problem gets worse and worse. And since that problem is getting worse, its cause other problems. <br>
<br>
Nothing can be changed without strife, but we are all afraid of causing strife.<br>
<br>
Prison population is growing by 3.9% each year. The more we put into prison the less we can afford to educate and help keep out of prison. And the wheels on the bus go round and round...round and round. <p><a href=mailto:Dandaelus@allakhazam.com>Dandaelus Wyldheart</a>
